1
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:35,033
Thie is the story
of a time long ago.

2
00:00:35,533 --> 00:00:38,567
A time of myth and legend,

3
00:00:38,567 --> 00:00:41,367
when the earth
was still young.

4
00:00:41,367 --> 00:00:44,600
The ancient gods
were petty and cruel,

5
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:47,133
and they played mankind
for their sport.

6
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:49,000
Aaaagh!

7
00:00:49,433 --> 00:00:52,100
Plaguing them with suffering,

8
00:00:52,100 --> 00:00:55,300
besieging them with terrors.

9
00:00:55,300 --> 00:00:57,167
( laughing )

10
00:00:57,167 --> 00:01:00,633
For centuries, the people
had nowhere to turn,

11
00:01:00,633 --> 00:01:03,633
no one to look to for help.

12
00:01:03,633 --> 00:01:06,100
Until... he arrived.

13
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:09,100
He was man
like no other.

14
00:01:09,100 --> 00:01:12,133
Born of a beautiful
mortal woman,

15
00:01:12,133 --> 00:01:15,600
but fathered by Zeus,
king of the gods.

16
00:01:16,067 --> 00:01:21,533
Hercules possessed  strength
the world had never seen,

17
00:01:21,933 --> 00:01:26,333
a strength surpassed
only by the power of his heart.

18
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:30,067
But everywhere he went he was
tormented by his stepmother,

19
00:01:30,067 --> 00:01:33,700
Hera, the all-powerful
queen of the gods.

20
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:38,067
Hera's eternal obsession
was to destroy Hercules,

21
00:01:38,067 --> 00:01:41,733
for he was the constant
living reminder of Zeus' infidelity.

22
00:02:03,267 --> 00:02:05,267
No matter the obstacle,

23
00:02:05,267 --> 00:02:08,867
as long as there were people
crying for help,

24
00:02:08,867 --> 00:02:12,467
there was one man
who would never rest:

25
00:02:12,467 --> 00:02:14,467
Hercules.

26
00:02:19,267 --> 00:02:21,267
( Dogs Barking )

27
00:02:30,467 --> 00:02:32,467
( Faint Rumbling )

28
00:02:38,267 --> 00:02:42,500
( Rumbling Increases )

29
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:46,633
( Sighing, Hissing,
Roaring Sounds )

30
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:53,500
# And the maidens #

31
00:02:53,900 --> 00:02:56,133
# Will cry #

32
00:02:56,133 --> 00:02:56,983
# To each other #

33
00:03:00,633 --> 00:03:02,567
- Ah, Median.
- Mmm.

34
00:03:02,967 --> 00:03:07,300
This time I'm gonna do it.
I'm really gonna do it.

35
00:03:07,300 --> 00:03:10,333
Don't do it on my boots.
They cost me five dinar.

36
00:03:10,733 --> 00:03:13,933
Ahh. No, you idiot.

37
00:03:13,933 --> 00:03:16,400
I'm gonna talk to her, to Critisa.

38
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:19,133
Yeah. You always say that.

39
00:03:19,133 --> 00:03:21,533
All you ever end up doing is pouring
more wine down your throat.

40
00:03:21,533 --> 00:03:23,333
Well, this time is different.

41
00:03:23,333 --> 00:03:25,600
There's her house.
I'm gonna go up to her window.

42
00:03:26,033 --> 00:03:29,633
And when she comes out
to see who it is,

43
00:03:30,033 --> 00:03:32,833
I'm gonna tell her I love her.

44
00:03:32,833 --> 00:03:34,833
You're crazy.

45
00:03:34,833 --> 00:03:37,067
What if that isn't Critisa's window?

46
00:03:37,067 --> 00:03:40,667
Why, then I'll pledge my love
to her sister...

47
00:03:40,667 --> 00:03:43,400
and hope that she's pretty.

48
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:45,900
( Rumbling, Distant Outcry )

49
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:50,300
Median, stop.

50
00:03:50,300 --> 00:03:54,300
- Lover boy chickens out again, huh?
- Ah, no. Look!

51
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:56,300
( Growling )

52
00:03:58,700 --> 00:03:59,900
Ahh.

53
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:01,900
Stay here.

54
00:04:04,700 --> 00:04:07,467
- ( Growling Continues )
- Ledus?

55
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:11,900
( Rumbling, Outcries )

56
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:17,833
( Coughing )

57
00:04:20,233 --> 00:04:22,633
( Choking )

58
00:04:24,433 --> 00:04:26,767
- Ledus!
- ( Coughing Continues )

59
00:04:27,167 --> 00:04:29,100
Ledus! Come on!

60
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:32,767
- We gotta get outta here!
- ( Loud Roaring )

61
00:04:33,567 --> 00:04:35,600
( Both Screaming )

62
00:04:42,233 --> 00:04:44,833
( Growling )

63
00:07:00,467 --> 00:07:02,467
( People Chattering )

64
00:07:03,667 --> 00:07:06,867
MAN: It's near the fresh cheese.

65
00:07:06,867 --> 00:07:10,467
WOMAN: Oh, come, come.

66
00:07:14,067 --> 00:07:15,900
Who are these men?

67
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:19,500
What do they bring
to your tiny town?

68
00:07:19,933 --> 00:07:21,933
Is it entertainment ?

69
00:07:22,333 --> 00:07:24,333
Is it opportunity?

70
00:07:25,133 --> 00:07:28,333
Perhaps it is the chance
to win a prize.

71
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:31,933
Well, ladies and gents,
we've brought you all three!

72
00:07:32,333 --> 00:07:35,133
If you wish-- No.

73
00:07:35,533 --> 00:07:37,167
If you dare,

74
00:07:37,167 --> 00:07:40,367
take a chance and step
into the ring...

75
00:07:40,767 --> 00:07:42,367
with Eryx the Boxer !

76
00:07:43,167 --> 00:07:45,900
- ( Puffing Rhythnically )
- ( Onlooker Laughs )

77
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:51,800
Hey, how much do we win
if we beat him?

78
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,800
Ah, that depends
on what you'll put up.

79
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:57,300
I'll pay you three times whatever
you're willing to wager.

80
00:07:57,300 --> 00:08:00,167
I've got two dinar that says I'll beat you
Eryx the Boxer.    - I've got three.

81
00:08:00,167 --> 00:08:03,667
- Five.
- Well, step into the ring, brave friend.

82
00:08:03,667 --> 00:08:07,167
- ( Boxer Puffing )
- But I warn you,

83
00:08:07,167 --> 00:08:11,100
Eryx the Boxer has never been beaten.

84
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:14,100
That's because he's never faced
any of us. ( Chuckles )

85
00:08:14,100 --> 00:08:16,600
Not so fast, friend.

86
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:19,100
You paid to fight Eryx the Boxer.

87
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:22,600
- ( Fighter Puffing )
- I thought this is Eryx the Boxer.

88
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:25,600
No, no, no.

89
00:08:26,100 --> 00:08:28,733
This is Eryx the Boxer.

90
00:08:29,533 --> 00:08:31,533
ONLOOKERS: Who? I don't see--

91
00:08:31,933 --> 00:08:35,500
( Onlookers Gasping,
Exclaining )

92
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:39,000
Wait. You tricked me.
This isn't fair.

93
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,900
( Growls )

94
00:08:40,900 --> 00:08:43,100
I thought the other guy was--

95
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,233
( Bone Breaking )

96
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:56,667
Who's next?

97
00:08:56,667 --> 00:08:59,933
You cheating bastard!
Sestus was my friend!

98
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:03,667
Well, come on! Come on.

99
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:06,700
No! Don't do it.

100
00:09:15,333 --> 00:09:17,967
( Bone Breaking, Flesh Ripping )

101
00:09:28,633 --> 00:09:31,400
( Laughing )

102
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:34,700
Quick. Go get Hercules.
We need help.

103
00:09:37,100 --> 00:09:39,900
( Dog Barking )

104
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:49,500
( Children Chattering )

105
00:09:56,867 --> 00:09:58,467
- I am not!
- I'm gonna get this time.

106
00:09:58,467 --> 00:10:00,467
I'm gonna get it
this time.

107
00:10:00,867 --> 00:10:03,667
- ( Lion Growling )
- There he is! There he is!

108
00:10:04,067 --> 00:10:08,067
( Boys Yelling, Lion Growling )

109
00:10:09,667 --> 00:10:13,267
- ( Barking )
- ( Growling, Yelling Continue )

110
00:10:13,267 --> 00:10:14,933
Kill the Lion! It got me!

111
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:17,333
BOYS: Kill him! Kill him!

112
00:10:24,133 --> 00:10:26,333
- ( Thud )
- ( Grunts )

113
00:10:26,333 --> 00:10:28,333
AESON: Kill it! Yeah!

114
00:10:28,333 --> 00:10:30,767
- Daddy?
- ( Roars )

115
00:10:31,567 --> 00:10:33,567
( Laughs )

116
00:10:34,367 --> 00:10:37,167
AESON: That was fun!
I didn't I scare us.

117
00:10:37,567 --> 00:10:39,967
- KLONUS: Can we do it again?
- ( Laughing )

118
00:10:45,833 --> 00:10:49,800
Hercules! Hercules!

119
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:51,400
Hercules!

120
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:54,467
We need you!

121
00:11:01,367 --> 00:11:02,567
( Laughing )

122
00:11:02,967 --> 00:11:04,567
- Who's next?
- MAN: Not I, sir.

123
00:11:04,967 --> 00:11:09,367
What about you? Or you? Huh?

124
00:11:09,367 --> 00:11:10,167
What about you?

125
00:11:10,567 --> 00:11:14,700
- What about me?
- It's about time.

126
00:11:14,700 --> 00:11:17,967
It was me you wanted, you didn't have
to kill all these innocent men.

127
00:11:18,367 --> 00:11:20,900
I had to find some way
to amuse myself.

128
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:25,867
- You hard look like the strongest man in
the world.   - Sorry to let you down.

129
00:11:25,867 --> 00:11:28,700
It doesn't matter. Your days are over!

130
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:31,267
Then let's stop talking
and start fighting.

131
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:40,233
( Grunts )

132
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:47,800
Son, you should have seen
that last one coming!

133
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:49,567
Put your left up and jab!
Jab! Come on!

134
00:12:04,933 --> 00:12:08,967
( Punches Landing, Grunts )

135
00:12:22,433 --> 00:12:26,433
- That your boy?
- No, no, I'm just a spectator.

136
00:12:26,433 --> 00:12:28,033
Come on! Pump one, left!

137
00:12:39,867 --> 00:12:42,267
( Bone Creaking )

138
00:12:42,267 --> 00:12:44,833
Oh, now he's got him.
Now he's got him!

139
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:48,100
- Ooh!
- He won't keep his left up.

140
00:12:52,667 --> 00:12:56,700
- Enough games, Hercules.
- I agree. Let's finish this.

141
00:12:56,700 --> 00:12:58,533
Ohh, watch. Watch, watch.

142
00:13:01,333 --> 00:13:02,700
Come on, Hercules!

143
00:13:05,733 --> 00:13:08,133
- You a fighter?
- Me a fighter? No, I just--

144
00:13:08,133 --> 00:13:12,267
- I just fight with the devil sometimes!
- ( Laughs )

145
00:13:22,167 --> 00:13:23,400
Right. Right!

146
00:13:28,167 --> 00:13:30,133
Oh, he's going better, eh?

147
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:52,600
Yes!

148
00:14:10,767 --> 00:14:12,667
( Yelling )

149
00:14:21,367 --> 00:14:23,367
You won, Hercules.

150
00:14:23,767 --> 00:14:24,967
You're entitled to a prize.

151
00:14:25,367 --> 00:14:28,567
- I don't want any prize from you.
- But this is special.

152
00:14:28,967 --> 00:14:32,967
It was pricked out just for you.

153
00:14:48,233 --> 00:14:49,833
( Coins Clinking )

154
00:14:53,433 --> 00:14:56,967
Hera, I thought we were through
with these games of yours.

155
00:14:56,967 --> 00:14:58,967
I don't want to battle
with you any longer.

156
00:14:59,467 --> 00:15:01,500
What do you say to a truce?

157
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:04,333
( Thunderclap )

158
00:15:04,733 --> 00:15:08,100
Fine. If that's how you want it, we
can always go back to the way it was.

159
00:15:28,167 --> 00:15:30,167
You were doing so well, my son.

160
00:15:30,567 --> 00:15:33,367
- Why did you let it end like that?
- She's lucky that's all I did!

161
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:37,367
- It'll only make her angrier.
- If you hadn't been unfaithful, she wouldn't be so mad.

162
00:15:37,367 --> 00:15:40,833
( Chuckles ) And you wouldn't
have been born.

163
00:15:42,333 --> 00:15:45,267
It doesn't make my life easier,
living under a curse.

164
00:15:45,767 --> 00:15:48,700
Curse? You've got
a warm bed to sleep in,

165
00:15:48,700 --> 00:15:50,700
a lovely wife, beautiful children.

166
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:53,133
That's more then most men have.

167
00:15:53,133 --> 00:15:54,633
That's more than I'll ever have.

168
00:15:55,133 --> 00:15:58,700
You should realize how--
how lucky you are!

169
00:15:58,700 --> 00:16:02,700
Yeah, I do.
Although I don't call it luck.

170
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:04,300
I've had to fight for what I have.

171
00:16:04,300 --> 00:16:08,367
You'll have to work twice as hard
to keep it. But it's worth it.

172
00:16:08,367 --> 00:16:09,767
And you know it.

173
00:16:10,733 --> 00:16:13,000
It's worth it.

174
00:16:13,433 --> 00:16:17,267
You know, you ought to
come and visit sometime.

175
00:16:17,267 --> 00:16:21,100
- I'll try. Promise.
- Okay.

176
00:16:21,933 --> 00:16:25,433
Hey! You were great today.

177
00:16:25,433 --> 00:16:29,200
But don't forget to jab,
jab a little more, and duck!

178
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:34,833
Don't forget to duck now
and then ( Chuckles )

179
00:16:41,567 --> 00:16:44,567
I should have known Eryx was
another one of Hera's tricks.

180
00:16:44,567 --> 00:16:48,067
What difference would it have made?
You would have gone anyway.

181
00:16:48,067 --> 00:16:52,067
- That's who you are. People call for help--
- And I always go. I know.

182
00:16:52,067 --> 00:16:55,067
- Yes.  - I can't stand to see the gods
play with people's lives,

183
00:16:55,067 --> 00:16:56,567
anybody's lives.

184
00:16:56,567 --> 00:16:58,067
I know that,

185
00:16:58,567 --> 00:17:01,067
and I love that about you.

186
00:17:05,567 --> 00:17:08,067
You got this from that great lion.

187
00:17:08,067 --> 00:17:13,000
What would the people of Nemea
have done if you hadn't killed it for them?

188
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:17,667
And the Hydra that tormented
the Lernaeans?

189
00:17:18,667 --> 00:17:22,167
What would have happened if you
hadn't have come to their aid?

190
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:25,667
And Tiphys.

191
00:17:25,667 --> 00:17:27,167
Mmm.

192
00:17:27,667 --> 00:17:31,667
Think of all the suffering he
caused until you stopped him.

193
00:17:33,533 --> 00:17:38,100
And do I have to remind you
what happened in Saenia?

194
00:17:51,100 --> 00:17:54,700
( Chickens Clucking,
Goats Bleating )

195
00:17:56,300 --> 00:17:59,900
( Metal Clinking Steadily )

196
00:18:11,067 --> 00:18:13,300
Nessus, what an I doing wrong?

197
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:17,400
Be patient, Hercules. You can't
just bully iron into shape.

198
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:19,400
You gotta mold it
Little by little, hmm?

199
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:21,467
Try heating it a little bit more.

200
00:18:24,467 --> 00:18:27,600
( Children Laughing, Chattering )

201
00:18:30,967 --> 00:18:33,200
( Chuckles ) Hercules.

202
00:18:35,233 --> 00:18:39,133
- Hey. Hercules!
- Huh?

203
00:18:39,133 --> 00:18:41,300
I think the harness
is hot enough now.

204
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:47,967
( Chuckles ) Yeah.

205
00:18:47,967 --> 00:18:50,367
I guess I sort of got distracted.

206
00:18:50,367 --> 00:18:53,233
Sometimes I just can't believe
they're mine. Know what I mean?

207
00:18:53,233 --> 00:18:56,667
Yeah. You're a lucky man, Hercules.

208
00:18:57,067 --> 00:18:59,467
Yeah. I'd say I am. Thanks.

209
00:19:01,867 --> 00:19:04,233
- ( Horse Whinnies )
- ( Snorts )

210
00:19:07,100 --> 00:19:08,700
( Clicking Tongue )

211
00:19:25,900 --> 00:19:29,500
Dad! There's a girl coming!

212
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:40,000
- Are you Hercules?
- Yes, I am.

213
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:43,567
What is it? What's wrong?

214
00:19:44,900 --> 00:19:46,900
- DEIANEIRA: What's happened?
- I don't know.

215
00:19:46,900 --> 00:19:48,500
Bring her inside, quickly.

216
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:05,233
- I need your help. Please!
- Here. Drink this.

217
00:20:08,533 --> 00:20:10,933
There isn't any time.

218
00:20:10,933 --> 00:20:13,733
I've traveled days and
nights to find Hercules.

219
00:20:13,733 --> 00:20:17,100
My village, Gryphon--
A hole has opened up.

220
00:20:17,100 --> 00:20:19,100
I-It's choking everything.

221
00:20:19,100 --> 00:20:22,833
- What do you mean? What kind of hole?
- A hole breathing death.

222
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:25,433
We've made sacrifices and offerings.

223
00:20:25,433 --> 00:20:29,633
- Nothing's been able to stop it.
- I'm not sure that I could help.

224
00:20:29,633 --> 00:20:32,900
You must! Please, you're our only hope.

225
00:20:33,367 --> 00:20:36,067
I've come all this way
to lead you back with me.

226
00:20:36,067 --> 00:20:40,033
- Please say you'll go.
- Get some rest.

227
00:20:40,033 --> 00:20:42,500
You need to sleep.

228
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:50,400
- MAN: What'll we drink to?
- To our protector, Hercules! May he live forever!

229
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:52,400
- To Hercules!
- ALL: To Hercules!

230
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:55,900
Hercules, Hercules, Hercules.

231
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:59,733
I'm gonna be sick if you all
don't shut up about Hercules.

232
00:20:59,733 --> 00:21:03,067
Aw, shut your hole, Nessus! Hercules is
the greatest! There's no disputing it!

233
00:21:03,067 --> 00:21:07,867
- None of us could even do a fraction of
what he does.  - NESSUS: Of course not.

234
00:21:07,867 --> 00:21:10,267
But we're not half-god, are we?

235
00:21:10,767 --> 00:21:13,200
I-I work and sweat and make
offerings every day,

236
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:16,667
and I'm barely gettin' by.

237
00:21:16,667 --> 00:21:19,800
How fair is that? You're blind.

238
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:24,867
You know that? All of you.
Just like Deianeira.

239
00:21:24,867 --> 00:21:28,067
She praises him and fawns over him.

240
00:21:28,067 --> 00:21:30,333
Like we can do no wrong.

241
00:21:30,333 --> 00:21:32,300
He doesn't deserve her.

242
00:21:32,300 --> 00:21:36,133
He's gone all the time, doing whatever
he can to make his name bigger.

243
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:39,000
I'm the one that takes care of her.

244
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:42,433
You better watch your mouth,
you idiot half-horse!

245
00:21:42,433 --> 00:21:45,233
If Hercules hears about what's
goin' on, there'll be trouble.

246
00:21:45,233 --> 00:21:49,233
- ( Mug Slams On Table )
- Damn Hercules. I-I-I'm not afraid of him.

247
00:21:49,733 --> 00:21:50,733
Not one bit.

248
00:21:51,233 --> 00:21:55,033
I have the Goddess Hera
to rely on. Hmm?

249
00:21:55,033 --> 00:21:57,333
She watches over me.
She's my protector.

250
00:21:57,833 --> 00:22:01,633
( Inhales ) I've had enough of all of you.

251
00:22:01,633 --> 00:22:06,533
I'm going home beofre I hear
his damn hame raised again.

252
00:22:09,033 --> 00:22:12,900
- ( Tail Slaps Table )
- ( Grunts )

253
00:22:21,300 --> 00:22:23,800
( Rustling Sound )

254
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:25,800
( Gasps ) Who's there?

255
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:27,100
Who is that?

256
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:33,867
What is it? Are you all right?
You're trembling.

257
00:22:34,267 --> 00:22:36,067
I thought I saw something
outside the window.

258
00:22:36,533 --> 00:22:40,033
Well, you're safe now.
There's nobody there.

259
00:22:40,033 --> 00:22:42,767
- I'm sorry. I didn't mean to wake you.
- Shh.

260
00:22:42,767 --> 00:22:46,833
Don't give it another thought.
Just lay bacl and try to get some sleep.

261
00:22:46,833 --> 00:22:49,267
Is Hercules gonna help my village?

262
00:22:49,267 --> 00:22:52,533
- Is he gonna come back with me?
- Yes, I think he is.

263
00:22:52,533 --> 00:22:55,767
Thank you. Thank both of you.

264
00:22:55,767 --> 00:22:57,200
Good night.

265
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:07,600
( Hammer Pinging )

266
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:22,000
( Hammering Continues )

267
00:23:24,433 --> 00:23:27,833
Nessus, what are you doing?

268
00:23:27,833 --> 00:23:28,733
Ahh. You see this?

269
00:23:32,633 --> 00:23:34,900
It's perfect.
Ah, it's absolutely perfect.

270
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:38,333
Yes. Well, let's
just leave it for now.

271
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:42,767
You don't believe me, do you? That I can
do something better than Hercules?

272
00:23:42,767 --> 00:23:46,967
( Sighs ) I believe you, Nessus.
It's just that it's late.

273
00:23:46,967 --> 00:23:50,267
I was surprised you could even sleep,
what with that girl here...

274
00:23:50,267 --> 00:23:53,867
- to take your precious husband away.
- Nessus, what's wrong with you?

275
00:23:53,867 --> 00:23:55,733
( Laughs ) With me?

276
00:23:55,733 --> 00:23:58,167
It's what's wrong with you
that's the problem!

277
00:23:58,567 --> 00:24:01,400
You don't really trust him, do you?

278
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:03,800
You can't really believe
that he'll be faithful.

279
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:06,600
My husband? I'm sure of it.

280
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:10,000
Oh, come on!
They'll be alone together.

281
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:12,800
And Hercules is what Hercules is.

282
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:16,000
Think. Her smooth skin,
her glowing hair,

283
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:21,300
- her youth.
- That's enough. Good night.

284
00:24:21,300 --> 00:24:25,333
I bet there's something else
I can do better than Hercules.

285
00:24:25,333 --> 00:24:27,167
( Grunts, Chuckles )

286
00:24:27,167 --> 00:24:30,200
Now get out of my way.

287
00:24:30,200 --> 00:24:32,133
Go sleep it off.

288
00:24:33,933 --> 00:24:36,833
He'll have her. You'll see.

289
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:41,800
( Exhales )

290
00:25:11,433 --> 00:25:13,833
( Woman Singing )

291
00:25:13,833 --> 00:25:16,233
Whoo! ( Laughs )

292
00:25:16,233 --> 00:25:18,233
Looks like a good day to travel.

293
00:25:18,633 --> 00:25:21,433
I was afraid we might have rain,
but it looks like we're be just fine.

294
00:25:21,433 --> 00:25:25,933
I hope that's enough
to get you there.

295
00:25:25,933 --> 00:25:29,433
Hey. What's wrong with you?

296
00:25:29,433 --> 00:25:31,933
Nothing. I'm fine. It's just--

297
00:25:33,433 --> 00:25:36,433
It's just that I'm gonna miss you,
that's all.

298
00:25:39,933 --> 00:25:41,933
I'm gonna miss you too.

299
00:25:43,933 --> 00:25:45,433
( Chuckles )

300
00:25:47,633 --> 00:25:50,833
- ( Growls )
- ( Laughs )

301
00:25:52,333 --> 00:25:54,267
Hey, Nessus. Let's go.

302
00:25:58,667 --> 00:26:01,567
Why don't you go give your dad
a big kiss goodbye, okay?

303
00:26:06,467 --> 00:26:08,900
I want to thank you for taking
such good care of me.

304
00:26:08,900 --> 00:26:11,300
I was in a pretty horrid state
when I arrived.

305
00:26:11,300 --> 00:26:13,300
It's nice to see that
you're feeling better today.

306
00:26:13,300 --> 00:26:17,733
Oh, here. I want you to have this.

307
00:26:17,733 --> 00:26:21,200
Absolutely not, Iole.
I can't accept this.

308
00:26:21,700 --> 00:26:23,367
Please, Deianeira.

309
00:26:23,367 --> 00:26:27,700
It would make me very happy
if you'd accept it and wear it.

310
00:26:27,700 --> 00:26:30,633
All right, then. I will. Thank you.

311
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:35,300
- You gonna be good? You promise?
- Yep.

312
00:26:35,300 --> 00:26:37,933
- Gonna miss me?
- No. ( Laughs )

313
00:26:43,333 --> 00:26:45,333
- You ready?
- Yeah.

314
00:26:53,767 --> 00:26:58,267
AESON: Bye, Dad. Come back soon.

315
00:27:03,267 --> 00:27:06,067
( Villagers Chattering )

316
00:27:14,867 --> 00:27:18,867
Chickens! Chickens! Here's chickens.

317
00:27:18,867 --> 00:27:20,833
Two dinar! Two dinar!

318
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:27,800
MAN: Fresh bread. Hot from the oven!

319
00:27:27,800 --> 00:27:30,300
You'll never buy better! Fresh bread.

320
00:27:30,300 --> 00:27:33,733
You get bread here now.
One dinar! Only one dinar.

321
00:27:33,733 --> 00:27:37,200
My deepest sympath. I'm so sorry.

322
00:27:37,200 --> 00:27:39,200
I don't know what you mean.

323
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:43,133
For the loss of your husband.
My condolences.

324
00:27:43,633 --> 00:27:48,067
- My husband's fine.
- But you have the medallion.

325
00:27:48,067 --> 00:27:50,067
That tells me you've lost your husband.

326
00:27:50,067 --> 00:27:51,567
This was just a gift.

327
00:27:51,567 --> 00:27:54,533
A gift from a sweet, beautiful girl?

328
00:27:54,533 --> 00:27:57,533
Yes. How do you know that?
Do you know her?

329
00:27:58,033 --> 00:27:58,533
I knew one like her once.

330
00:27:58,533 --> 00:28:02,467
She's a Nurian Maiden.

331
00:28:02,967 --> 00:28:05,400
- Still, why would you think my husband was dead?
- When a task need be done.

332
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:09,333
These beautiful virgins can
persuade a man to attempt it.

333
00:28:09,833 --> 00:28:14,333
No, not Hercules. She has no power
over him. If you'll excuse me.

334
00:28:14,333 --> 00:28:16,767
She has power over all men.

335
00:28:16,767 --> 00:28:20,700
From the moment of birth, she's
trained for this and only this.

336
00:28:20,700 --> 00:28:25,167
She knows all there is to know
about love, charm...

337
00:28:25,667 --> 00:28:27,167
and seduction.

338
00:28:27,633 --> 00:28:31,133
She'll make your husband
fall in love with her.

339
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:33,600
And when he does,

340
00:28:34,100 --> 00:28:36,600
he'll do everything she asks,

341
00:28:37,100 --> 00:28:40,600
even though it leads him
to his death.

342
00:28:41,100 --> 00:28:44,567
No, you're wrong.
This medallion doesn't mean anything.

343
00:28:44,567 --> 00:28:48,500
I tried to tell myself that once.
( Gasps )

344
00:28:52,933 --> 00:28:56,433
Deianeira, I don't think you should go.
She's just some old crazy woman.

345
00:28:56,433 --> 00:28:58,933
But the things that she said!
She knew!

346
00:28:58,933 --> 00:29:00,433
And I have to warn Hercules.

347
00:29:00,933 --> 00:29:03,433
But it could be dangerous, and you're
not even sure you know the right way.

348
00:29:03,433 --> 00:29:06,933
Please, just take care of the children.
That's all I'm asking.

349
00:29:13,867 --> 00:29:16,367
- Aeson, come here.
- Why?

350
00:29:16,367 --> 00:29:19,767
I have to go away for a while,
but I'll be back soon.

351
00:29:19,767 --> 00:29:21,967
Your Aunt Althea's gonna take care
of you, but you're a big boy.

352
00:29:21,967 --> 00:29:24,133
- You're gonna take care of your brother
and sister.     - Okay.

353
00:29:24,133 --> 00:29:27,433
- I love you.
- I love you too, Mom.

354
00:29:27,933 --> 00:29:29,233
- Bye, sweetie.
- Bye.

355
00:29:39,633 --> 00:29:42,833
- How's it look down there? Any better?
This is probably?        - No!

356
00:29:43,233 --> 00:29:45,633
I've been all the way to
the bend. It only gets deeper.

357
00:29:46,833 --> 00:29:51,667
This is probably the best spot
to cross. I'll get Iole.

358
00:29:51,667 --> 00:29:56,467
Your beauty's so strong
it charms even the animals.

359
00:29:56,467 --> 00:29:58,867
It shouldn't surprise me.

360
00:29:58,867 --> 00:30:01,267
Deianeira, what's wrong?

361
00:30:01,267 --> 00:30:06,600
I know all about you, Iole. I know
about your breeding your training,

362
00:30:06,600 --> 00:30:09,800
and how you have the power
to make men fall in love,

363
00:30:09,800 --> 00:30:13,833
how you'll make a widow
and orphans out of a loving family.

364
00:30:13,833 --> 00:30:15,267
But please, call this off.

365
00:30:15,767 --> 00:30:17,500
Leave my family be.

366
00:30:17,500 --> 00:30:18,467
I can't.

367
00:30:28,067 --> 00:30:30,900
- ( Footsteps )
- Deianeira, what are you doing here?

368
00:30:30,900 --> 00:30:34,233
I've come to warn you.
Thank the gods, you're all right!

369
00:30:34,233 --> 00:30:35,733
Warn me? What are you talking about?

370
00:30:35,733 --> 00:30:37,733
You've been tricked.
We've both been tricked.

371
00:30:37,733 --> 00:30:42,633
You know this medallion, the one
Iole gave me? She's Nurian Maiden.

372
00:30:43,133 --> 00:30:45,967
Deianeira, I know. I've known
since she first arrived.

373
00:30:45,967 --> 00:30:48,967
- And you're still going with her?
- It'll be all right.

374
00:30:48,967 --> 00:30:51,900
But she'll take you away from us
and we'll never see you again!

375
00:30:51,900 --> 00:30:54,900
Please, please, come home.
She has these powers.

376
00:30:54,900 --> 00:30:57,867
and she'll make you fall in love,
and you'll be willing to die for her.

377
00:30:57,867 --> 00:31:01,367
All this talk about powers
and dying, it's nonsense.

378
00:31:01,367 --> 00:31:04,033
There's only one person in the world
I'd die for, and that's you.

379
00:31:04,533 --> 00:31:06,467
Let me go and go what
I can for Iole's people.

380
00:31:06,467 --> 00:31:08,967
Then I'll hurry right back home
to you. I promise.

381
00:31:09,467 --> 00:31:15,667
At the very worst, I'll have
a new scar or two to show you.

382
00:31:18,567 --> 00:31:21,033
Now get yourself home.

383
00:31:21,033 --> 00:31:25,267
Nessus will go with you to
make sure you get there safely.

384
00:31:25,267 --> 00:31:26,667
We better get going.

385
00:31:31,167 --> 00:31:32,667
Good-bye.

386
00:31:40,233 --> 00:31:45,967
Funny, isn't it? You travel all this
way because you love him so much.

387
00:31:46,367 --> 00:31:48,367
And still, where are you? Alone.

388
00:31:48,767 --> 00:31:51,167
Watching as he leaves with
her for a second time.

389
00:31:51,167 --> 00:31:55,967
Nessus, be quiet.
Hercules has a job to do.

390
00:31:56,433 --> 00:31:59,767
But why this job? Ask yourself that.

391
00:32:01,267 --> 00:32:04,833
Why has he chosen to
abandon his family...

392
00:32:05,233 --> 00:32:08,867
and go off risking his life
for this stranger?

393
00:32:08,867 --> 00:32:12,633
Could it be. Because she's a young,

394
00:32:12,633 --> 00:32:14,900
beautiful virgin?

395
00:32:14,900 --> 00:32:17,833
Mmm? Look at the way he carries her.

396
00:32:17,833 --> 00:32:21,833
The way he holds her, it's tender.

397
00:32:21,833 --> 00:32:25,833
Like a lover.
He used to carry you that way.

398
00:32:25,833 --> 00:32:29,467
Do you remember? Hmm?
Or is it too long ago?

399
00:32:29,900 --> 00:32:33,200
It's time to go. ( Gasps )

400
00:32:33,200 --> 00:32:35,633
If you were mine, Deianeira,
You'd never be alone.

401
00:32:35,633 --> 00:32:36,900
Let's go of me right now,

402
00:32:36,900 --> 00:32:41,267
or when Hercules gets home I will
tell him about this and the other night!

403
00:32:41,267 --> 00:32:44,400
There's only one way
to get through to you.

404
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:49,233
- One way to make you see things clearly,
like I do.   - Nessus, stop it!

405
00:32:49,233 --> 00:32:52,467
I should have done this
a long time ago.

406
00:32:58,367 --> 00:33:00,333
There's no escape, and you know it.

407
00:33:00,833 --> 00:33:03,833
So relax. You just might enjoy it.

408
00:33:04,333 --> 00:33:07,300
Hercules! Help! Hercules!

409
00:33:07,300 --> 00:33:10,233
What are you screaming about?

410
00:33:10,633 --> 00:33:14,467
DEIANEIRA: Help! Help!

411
00:33:14,467 --> 00:33:16,733
There is no Hercules!

412
00:33:16,733 --> 00:33:19,133
- Hercules, what is it?
- Keep quiet.

413
00:33:19,133 --> 00:33:21,467
- DEIANEIRA: Hercules!
- NESSUS: He's gone.

414
00:33:21,867 --> 00:33:26,233
- He's as good as dea--
- ( Arrow Thuds )

415
00:33:32,667 --> 00:33:34,267
( Grunting )

416
00:33:37,133 --> 00:33:38,633
( Gasping ) Hera.

417
00:33:39,133 --> 00:33:41,633
I'm dying.

418
00:33:41,633 --> 00:33:44,133
You were supposed to protect me.

419
00:33:44,133 --> 00:33:46,567
( Thunderclap )

420
00:33:48,033 --> 00:33:54,500
Deianeira. What vile thing have
I become to have done this to you?

421
00:33:54,500 --> 00:33:57,300
To end up like this. ( Gasps )

422
00:33:57,300 --> 00:33:59,333
It was only because I love you.

423
00:33:59,733 --> 00:34:02,500
I couldn't stand knowing the pain,

424
00:34:02,500 --> 00:34:05,133
the unhappiness he'd bring you.

425
00:34:05,133 --> 00:34:08,800
But he won't, he'll be true to me.

426
00:34:08,800 --> 00:34:12,567
- There is a way you can be sure of that.
- But I am sure.

427
00:34:12,567 --> 00:34:14,067
Listen to me.

428
00:34:14,067 --> 00:34:18,067
My blood is a powerful potion.
( Choking )

429
00:34:18,067 --> 00:34:20,067
Give the cloak to Hercules.

430
00:34:20,067 --> 00:34:23,733
Once he puts it on, he'll
never be unfaithful to you.

431
00:34:23,733 --> 00:34:26,367
I told you, I don't doubt him.

432
00:34:26,367 --> 00:34:27,567
But you do!

433
00:34:32,167 --> 00:34:35,967
Be sure. Give it to him.

434
00:34:37,900 --> 00:34:40,133
( Gasping )

435
00:34:47,100 --> 00:34:50,000
Deianeira! Are you all right?

436
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:50,800
I'm fine.

437
00:34:51,267 --> 00:34:54,767
- This is my fault.
- No, everything's okay.

438
00:34:54,767 --> 00:34:58,167
- We'll head back hom tonight.
-No, you just go on.

439
00:34:58,167 --> 00:35:00,533
- Deianeira, I'm not.
- No. You must go on.

440
00:35:00,533 --> 00:35:01,467
Hercules?

441
00:35:04,800 --> 00:35:05,700
And then take this.

442
00:35:06,200 --> 00:35:10,600
And when it gets cold at night, I want you
to wrap this around you and think only of me.

443
00:35:12,100 --> 00:35:14,600
I'll think of nothing else.

444
00:35:40,667 --> 00:35:44,033
( Rumbling, Howling Sounds )

445
00:35:54,133 --> 00:35:56,033
( Roaring Sounds )

446
00:36:04,167 --> 00:36:07,400
I'm tired of talking about me.
I want to hear more about you.

447
00:36:07,800 --> 00:36:10,600
Tell me some stories
about the great Hercules.

448
00:36:10,600 --> 00:36:13,400
Ah, there's not that much to tell.
I just do what I do.

449
00:36:13,800 --> 00:36:17,400
Besides, I want to know more about
your being a Nurian Maiden.

450
00:36:17,400 --> 00:36:21,967
You haven't told me why you
decided to become one.

451
00:36:21,967 --> 00:36:24,100
Well, it wasn't really my decision.

452
00:36:24,500 --> 00:36:26,800
Before I was born,
my mother had a vision...

453
00:36:27,300 --> 00:36:30,300
that I'd be called upon
to save my village.

454
00:36:30,300 --> 00:36:33,300
- I was wearing a blue stone medallion.
- Hmm.

455
00:36:33,300 --> 00:36:36,800
So she and my father sent me off
to train as a Nurian Maiden.

456
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:39,300
And here I am.

457
00:36:39,300 --> 00:36:41,800
What about the stories I have heard
of your special powers and all that?

458
00:36:41,800 --> 00:36:47,833
That's nonsense. Fools' talk. you,
of all people, must know how that is.

459
00:36:47,833 --> 00:36:52,233
According to the stories about the
great and powerful Hercules,

460
00:36:52,233 --> 00:36:55,033
- You're supposed to be ten feet tall.
- Hmm.

461
00:36:55,033 --> 00:36:58,233
Some of the crazy things
they say you've done!

462
00:36:58,233 --> 00:37:01,833
Do you know that you supposedly
slew a two-headed giant?

463
00:37:02,233 --> 00:37:05,600
You killed the Lernaean Hydra
by yourself.

464
00:37:05,600 --> 00:37:08,100
Or best of all, someone once told me...

465
00:37:08,100 --> 00:37:12,100
that you killed Anienormous sea monster by
squeezing its heart until it stopped beating!

466
00:37:13,533 --> 00:37:15,533
But those stories are true.

467
00:37:17,033 --> 00:37:19,467
No. I-- I mean it.
I really did all those things.

468
00:37:19,467 --> 00:37:22,633
So maybe Hercules does have
a tale or two after all.

469
00:37:24,633 --> 00:37:27,633
Come on. Tell me a few more.

470
00:37:27,633 --> 00:37:30,833
( Chuckles ) That's enough stories.
We'd better get to Gryphon.

471
00:37:49,933 --> 00:37:53,733
Oh, look. There's an inn.
We can get something to eat.

472
00:37:55,600 --> 00:37:59,533
( Man Growling, Dog Barking )

473
00:37:59,533 --> 00:38:01,967
I think you'd better stay out here.

474
00:38:03,967 --> 00:38:07,033
( Growling Continues )

475
00:38:07,533 --> 00:38:11,400
- ( Crash )
- ( Growling, Snarling )

476
00:38:21,733 --> 00:38:23,733
( Woman Screams )

477
00:38:24,733 --> 00:38:26,233
- What happening here?
- I don't know.

478
00:38:26,233 --> 00:38:30,433
Came in, set down his soup; then out
of the blue he starts screamin'!

479
00:38:30,933 --> 00:38:33,300
He just went crazy!
Started smashing the place up.

480
00:38:33,800 --> 00:38:36,700
- Did he say what he was mad about?
- No! He didn't say anything.

481
00:38:36,700 --> 00:38:38,167
( Snarling )

482
00:38:39,667 --> 00:38:42,033
Hey! Now, that's enough.

483
00:38:42,533 --> 00:38:44,533
- ( Snarling )
- Stop!

484
00:38:44,533 --> 00:38:46,933
- Iole, what are you doing?
- You're only scaring him.

485
00:38:46,933 --> 00:38:52,267
Scaring him? He's gone crazy. He'll turn
this place into splinters if I don't stop him!

486
00:38:52,267 --> 00:38:55,167
No, please. Put the club down.
Let me talk to him.

487
00:38:55,667 --> 00:38:59,500
Hercules! Put the club down.

488
00:39:07,700 --> 00:39:11,067
It's all right. I'm not gonna hurt you.

489
00:39:11,067 --> 00:39:13,067
It's all right.

490
00:39:22,167 --> 00:39:26,467
There, there. What's the matter?

491
00:39:26,467 --> 00:39:28,900
( Whimpering )

492
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:32,933
I think he burned his mouth
on his food.

493
00:39:33,433 --> 00:39:36,133
He would have said something,
but he can't speak.

494
00:39:36,133 --> 00:39:38,067
Can someone get him some water?

495
00:40:00,667 --> 00:40:02,667
Not everything needs to be killed.

496
00:40:03,100 --> 00:40:05,400
Sometimes kindness can work too.

497
00:40:27,033 --> 00:40:29,033
- ( Gasps )
- Oh! Be careful.

498
00:40:29,033 --> 00:40:31,867
- Are you all right?
- Yeah. Thanks.

499
00:40:37,133 --> 00:40:39,267
IOLE: Come on.

500
00:40:44,700 --> 00:40:47,500
IOLE: It's beautiful, isn't it?

501
00:40:47,500 --> 00:40:50,700
Yeah. A lot of stars out tonight.

502
00:40:51,900 --> 00:40:53,900
Myrea and Martumus.

503
00:40:53,900 --> 00:40:56,300
Every time I see them,
it makes me sad.

504
00:40:57,900 --> 00:41:01,500
- Which ones are they?
- Right up there.

505
00:41:02,300 --> 00:41:05,100
- Right where?
- Right up there.

506
00:41:05,100 --> 00:41:07,500
Here, I'll show you.

507
00:41:15,500 --> 00:41:18,700
They were lovers once--
or would have been.

508
00:41:18,700 --> 00:41:21,500
Their families were at war
and kept them apart.

509
00:41:21,500 --> 00:41:23,900
They were never allowed
to see each other,

510
00:41:24,300 --> 00:41:26,700
never allowed to touch.

511
00:41:26,700 --> 00:41:30,300
- Why didn't they just run away?
- They were going to.

512
00:41:30,300 --> 00:41:35,100
They had it all planned out. They were gonna
meet in the meadow and finally be together.

513
00:41:35,100 --> 00:41:37,900
Myrea's father found out.
He was so enraged.

514
00:41:37,900 --> 00:41:42,300
When Myrea refused to denounce
her love for Martumus.

515
00:41:42,300 --> 00:41:45,900
He was so filled with spite
that he killed her.

516
00:41:45,900 --> 00:41:48,300
- He killed his own daughter?
- Uh-huh.

517
00:41:48,300 --> 00:41:52,300
He tossed her body into the heavens.
See? That's her, reaching out.

518
00:41:52,300 --> 00:41:54,700
HERCULES:
And what happened to Martumus?

519
00:41:54,700 --> 00:41:57,900
Well, he wnet down to the
meadow to wait for her.

520
00:41:58,300 --> 00:42:00,300
Naturally, she never came.

521
00:42:00,700 --> 00:42:04,300
And then, by chance, he looked up
into the sky, and there she was.

522
00:42:04,300 --> 00:42:09,100
What did he do? Did he get revenge?
Did he kill her father?

523
00:42:09,500 --> 00:42:13,500
No. He was so wracked with grief...

524
00:42:13,500 --> 00:42:16,700
That he drew his dagger
and cut his own heart out.

525
00:42:16,700 --> 00:42:19,100
He had to stop the pain.

526
00:42:19,100 --> 00:42:21,900
Luckily, the gods saw what happened.

527
00:42:21,900 --> 00:42:25,100
Out of pity, they drew his body
up into the heavens.

528
00:42:25,100 --> 00:42:30,300
See? That's him, reaching out
towards Myrea.

529
00:42:31,900 --> 00:42:33,900
HERCULES: But they're not touching.

530
00:42:34,300 --> 00:42:35,500
No.

531
00:42:35,900 --> 00:42:38,300
In a cruel twist of fate,

532
00:42:38,300 --> 00:42:40,700
he landed just out of reach of her.

533
00:42:40,700 --> 00:42:43,500
And that's how they'll spend eternity.

534
00:42:43,500 --> 00:42:48,700
They know they'll never touch,
but they'll never stop trying.

535
00:42:48,700 --> 00:42:52,300
It's sad, isn't it?

536
00:42:53,900 --> 00:42:57,500
I guess I'm just silly.

537
00:42:58,700 --> 00:42:59,900
Good night, Hercules.

538
00:43:11,900 --> 00:43:17,100
Yeah. Uh, good night, Iole.

539
00:43:57,633 --> 00:43:59,233
( Rock Thuds )

540
00:44:01,633 --> 00:44:04,833
Hercules! You know you
shouldn't be watching me.

541
00:44:38,067 --> 00:44:41,667
HERCULES: Come on, Iole!
It's getting late.

542
00:44:51,500 --> 00:44:53,100
- Iole!
- ( Grunts )

543
00:44:54,433 --> 00:44:56,100
You don't deserve to love,
you bastard!

544
00:44:58,733 --> 00:45:02,467
Whoa! Who are you, friend?
Why are you attacking me?

545
00:45:02,467 --> 00:45:03,667
I'm not your friend!

546
00:45:03,667 --> 00:45:07,900
Fine! But what's your name, kid?
I like to know who's tryin' to kill me.

547
00:45:07,900 --> 00:45:09,800
I'm not a kid, either.

548
00:45:09,800 --> 00:45:14,600
You're not, but I don't
remember crossing you.

549
00:45:14,600 --> 00:45:16,600
Doesn't matter. You'll
remember dying by my hand!

550
00:45:20,133 --> 00:45:24,367
Now, that's enough! I'm not
gonna dirty my fists on you.

551
00:45:24,367 --> 00:45:26,267
- You're not?
- No.

552
00:45:26,267 --> 00:45:28,200
You can go find someone else to kill.

553
00:45:28,200 --> 00:45:31,567
- ( Spear Cracking )
- Now, I'm warning you.

554
00:45:31,567 --> 00:45:33,433
The next thing to break is your neck.

555
00:45:35,900 --> 00:45:38,267
- ( Attacker Grunts )
- ( Weapon Cracking )

556
00:45:38,767 --> 00:45:40,667
Hercules, don't kill him!

557
00:45:48,667 --> 00:45:52,567
- Poor Lycastus!
- Is there something you want to tell me?

558
00:45:52,567 --> 00:45:54,767
I told him not to follow me,
but he can't help it.

559
00:45:55,167 --> 00:45:57,533
- He doesn't understand.
- Doesn't understand what?

560
00:45:57,533 --> 00:46:00,000
That even though I love him.
There isn't a future for us.

561
00:46:00,500 --> 00:46:04,367
- Well, why not?
- There can't be. It's not in my destiny.

562
00:46:04,367 --> 00:46:07,833
But if you love him,
and he obviously loves you--

563
00:46:07,833 --> 00:46:11,800
It doesn't matter. There are more
important things in the world.

564
00:46:11,800 --> 00:46:14,767
My life and his life mean nothing.

565
00:46:14,767 --> 00:46:17,267
I don't want this to affect
anything, Hercules.

566
00:46:17,767 --> 00:46:20,700
Saving my village is still the only
thing that matters to me.

567
00:46:20,700 --> 00:46:23,200
Come on. Let's go.

568
00:46:23,200 --> 00:46:25,700
My town isn't that far off.

569
00:46:33,233 --> 00:46:36,033
( Moans )

570
00:46:50,833 --> 00:46:52,933
We're close now. It's just up here.

571
00:46:56,600 --> 00:47:00,100
There it is. It's even worse
than when I left it.

572
00:47:04,867 --> 00:47:07,300
( Villagers Chattering )

573
00:47:07,300 --> 00:47:10,067
Get out. Out, Vito.

574
00:47:15,467 --> 00:47:17,300
It's him!

575
00:47:17,767 --> 00:47:23,267
Iole's back, and she's
brought Hercules with her!

576
00:47:23,267 --> 00:47:25,667
- Hercules!
- MAN: Hercules!

577
00:47:25,667 --> 00:47:27,267
You'll save us now!

578
00:47:27,267 --> 00:47:30,100
He's the strongest man in the world!

579
00:47:30,100 --> 00:47:33,400
Come with us, Hercules.
We'll take you to it.

580
00:47:49,067 --> 00:47:51,467
( Villagers Chattering )

581
00:48:11,833 --> 00:48:14,333
( Nearby Roaring Sound )

582
00:48:33,167 --> 00:48:35,600
( Distorted Weeping )

583
00:48:53,600 --> 00:48:56,100
( Weeping Continues )

584
00:49:04,000 --> 00:49:05,967
( Distorted Laughter )

585
00:49:05,967 --> 00:49:08,400
( Screeching )

586
00:49:16,167 --> 00:49:18,133
( Roaring Sounds, Voices Screeching )

587
00:49:23,133 --> 00:49:25,433
( Roaring )

588
00:49:27,867 --> 00:49:31,633
( Screeching )

589
00:49:43,467 --> 00:49:46,200
( Wicked Laughter )

590
00:49:52,900 --> 00:49:54,567
What is this thing?

591
00:49:54,567 --> 00:49:58,000
That's the Underworld. There's
nothing down there but death.

592
00:50:00,000 --> 00:50:02,933
I need to know something.

593
00:50:02,933 --> 00:50:05,333
Am I immortal or not?

594
00:50:05,733 --> 00:50:08,200
- Hercules--
- I've never asked you before.

595
00:50:08,600 --> 00:50:11,400
But as your son. I'm asking you now.

596
00:50:13,400 --> 00:50:14,600
Can I die?

597
00:50:15,000 --> 00:50:17,733
- You don't wanna know.
- I have to know.

598
00:50:17,733 --> 00:50:20,233
You're a god, my mother's mortal
what does that make me?

599
00:50:20,733 --> 00:50:22,733
It's a question you should't
be asking.

600
00:50:22,733 --> 00:50:25,167
But I have to know what will
happen if I go into that hole.

601
00:50:25,167 --> 00:50:26,600
Will I ever get back hole again?

602
00:50:27,100 --> 00:50:30,600
So don't go into the hole!
Go home right now.

603
00:50:30,600 --> 00:50:35,567
You don't have to save this town!
You don't owe anything to these people!

604
00:50:35,967 --> 00:50:37,933
Just turn around and leave!

605
00:50:37,933 --> 00:50:40,933
Go home and grow old with
your family like you intended to.

606
00:50:40,933 --> 00:50:45,733
Tell me. Damn it, Father! Tell me!

607
00:50:48,733 --> 00:50:53,200
All right. You are mortal.

608
00:50:54,000 --> 00:50:56,967
Hercules...

609
00:50:57,467 --> 00:50:59,567
you can die.

610
00:50:59,967 --> 00:51:04,233
How do I know you're
telling the truth?

611
00:51:04,233 --> 00:51:07,933
- Why would I lie?
- To keep me out of that hole.

612
00:51:08,333 --> 00:51:11,167
You're afraid what might
happen to me.

613
00:51:11,667 --> 00:51:14,167
You wanted an answer.
I gave you an answer!

614
00:51:14,667 --> 00:51:18,167
Who knows if it's...

615
00:51:18,167 --> 00:51:20,300
the right one?

616
00:51:20,300 --> 00:51:23,100
( Distorted Scream )

617
00:51:23,100 --> 00:51:25,100
( Roaring )

618
00:51:25,100 --> 00:51:27,600
- What's he doing?
- He's just standing there.

619
00:51:27,600 --> 00:51:30,367
- MAN: Why isn't he doing anything?
- You know your fate if he fails.

620
00:51:36,167 --> 00:51:40,400
You're getting ready for him,
aren't you?

621
00:51:40,400 --> 00:51:43,367
Please, Iole.

622
00:51:43,367 --> 00:51:44,967
Don't.

623
00:51:45,367 --> 00:51:48,167
Lycastus, you've always
known this day would come.

624
00:51:48,567 --> 00:51:49,800
This is my destiny.

625
00:51:50,300 --> 00:51:52,300
I thought you loved me.

626
00:51:54,300 --> 00:51:56,300
I do love you.

627
00:51:56,300 --> 00:51:59,700
And if you love me, you'll let
me do what I have to do.

628
00:51:59,700 --> 00:52:03,200
- What about us?
- There is no us.

629
00:52:05,200 --> 00:52:06,700
( Gasps )

630
00:52:14,200 --> 00:52:16,567
No! We can't. I can't.

631
00:52:16,567 --> 00:52:19,300
- But you want to.
- HERCULES: Iole.

632
00:52:20,633 --> 00:52:23,133
You've gotta hide, quick.

633
00:52:30,533 --> 00:52:32,533
Hercules, I've been waiting for you.

634
00:52:32,533 --> 00:52:35,533
Iole, I'm afraid I can't help your town.

635
00:52:35,533 --> 00:52:40,333
I stood on the edge of that hole,
and I thought about it long and hard.

636
00:52:40,833 --> 00:52:43,733
If I go down there,
I may never come back.

637
00:52:45,733 --> 00:52:49,733
I have children now, and a wife I love.

638
00:52:49,733 --> 00:52:52,233
I have to live for them.

639
00:52:52,233 --> 00:52:55,567
Hercules, my people suffer.

640
00:52:55,567 --> 00:52:59,867
They need you. I need you.

641
00:53:02,367 --> 00:53:04,700
Iole, I can't.

642
00:53:06,700 --> 00:53:10,033
Please, won't you do it for me?

643
00:53:24,200 --> 00:53:26,100
Say you'll do it for me.

644
00:53:27,600 --> 00:53:30,700
No! Please, don't.

645
00:53:30,700 --> 00:53:35,367
I have to go home
and be with my family.

646
00:53:35,367 --> 00:53:38,700
I don't want anything more to do
with the gods and their games.

647
00:53:38,700 --> 00:53:42,267
- I just want to be left alone.
- If you're not gonna save my town, then I will.

648
00:53:42,267 --> 00:53:47,000
- I'll go in that hole.
- No, you won't. It wouldn't do any good.

649
00:53:47,000 --> 00:53:48,733
You'd only be killed.

650
00:53:48,733 --> 00:53:52,033
It doesn't matter. I'm dead anyway.

651
00:53:52,033 --> 00:53:55,733
I failed my mission, and I'm dead.

652
00:53:55,733 --> 00:53:57,633
I'm sorry.

653
00:54:01,400 --> 00:54:03,267
Lycastus.

654
00:54:08,700 --> 00:54:11,500
You take care of her, my friend.

655
00:54:37,200 --> 00:54:41,600
( Cloak Whooshing, Whipping )

656
00:54:45,933 --> 00:54:47,433
Aah!

657
00:54:49,367 --> 00:54:51,200
- ( Whipping Sounds )
- Aaah!

658
00:54:58,067 --> 00:55:00,033
Aaah, aaah!

659
00:55:07,867 --> 00:55:09,300
Help him!

660
00:55:09,300 --> 00:55:13,167
- ( Sizzling Sound )
- ( Gasping )

661
00:55:13,167 --> 00:55:14,600
( Hercules Crying Out )

662
00:55:20,067 --> 00:55:22,767
( Screaming )

663
00:55:22,767 --> 00:55:24,633
( Explosion )

664
00:55:29,667 --> 00:55:32,200
The gods will never stop!

665
00:55:35,733 --> 00:55:37,667
( Roaring )

666
00:55:44,367 --> 00:55:48,233
( Panting, Yelling ) Hera-a-a!

667
00:55:48,633 --> 00:55:50,200
( Woman Screams )

668
00:55:52,600 --> 00:55:56,200
Mommy, Mommy! Daddy's coming home!

669
00:56:02,600 --> 00:56:05,400
Come on, let's go inside.
Go! Go! Right away.

670
00:56:08,600 --> 00:56:10,933
( Panting )

671
00:56:13,433 --> 00:56:15,867
He's dead, isn't he?

672
00:56:15,867 --> 00:56:19,100
My husband? He's dead?

673
00:56:20,600 --> 00:56:21,600
How?

674
00:56:23,067 --> 00:56:24,567
What happened?

675
00:56:24,567 --> 00:56:29,000
It was a cloak, a cursed cloak.

676
00:56:31,500 --> 00:56:33,500
He put it on and it tortured him,

677
00:56:34,000 --> 00:56:36,500
drove him mad.

678
00:56:36,500 --> 00:56:39,433
( Panting ) His only escape...

679
00:56:39,433 --> 00:56:42,300
was to jump into the hole.

680
00:56:45,300 --> 00:56:47,800
That cloak was supposed to
protect him.

681
00:56:48,300 --> 00:56:51,567
It was supposed to protect us!

682
00:56:51,567 --> 00:56:54,067
( Sobs ) I've killed him.

683
00:57:02,933 --> 00:57:04,013
( Moans )

684
00:57:14,500 --> 00:57:18,500
( Faint Roaring,
Faint Distorted Voices )

685
00:57:33,267 --> 00:57:38,100
HERCULES: Hey, you there.
Where am I? What is this place?

686
00:57:38,500 --> 00:57:40,900
Answer me. I'm talk to you.

687
00:57:40,900 --> 00:57:44,700
Oh, you're talking to me.
Of course you're talking to me.

688
00:57:44,700 --> 00:57:46,700
Who else in Hades?
I'm the only one here.

689
00:57:47,100 --> 00:57:48,500
Well, where is "Here"?

690
00:57:52,200 --> 00:57:55,533
It is, uh, customary to pay
the Boatman for passage.

691
00:57:56,433 --> 00:57:59,900
Huh? Wait, what are you doin' here?

692
00:57:59,900 --> 00:58:02,167
- You can't go across!
- Why not?

693
00:58:02,167 --> 00:58:06,100
Why not? Because you're still alive.
That's why not.

694
00:58:06,500 --> 00:58:09,600
Only the dead are permitted
to cross the River Styx.

695
00:58:10,000 --> 00:58:13,833
Well, we're gonna chance
that right now, aren't we?

696
00:58:13,833 --> 00:58:15,667
No, no, no, no. We can't.

697
00:58:15,667 --> 00:58:19,800
- "Can't"?
- When I say "can't,"

698
00:58:19,800 --> 00:58:22,800
I mean, you're a regular kind
of guy, I guess, uh--

699
00:58:22,800 --> 00:58:25,700
We could, uh, maybe talk. Yeah. Okay.

700
00:58:25,700 --> 00:58:30,133
BOATMAN: Hades is not gonna be
happy about this, let me tell you.

701
00:58:30,133 --> 00:58:32,633
No one alive has ever
entered the Underworld before.

702
00:58:33,133 --> 00:58:36,133
You're gonna be in bug trouble
when he hears about this.

703
00:58:36,133 --> 00:58:38,800
What am I sayin'?
I'm gonna be in big trouble.

704
00:58:40,800 --> 00:58:44,133
I don't know why someone who's
alive would wanna come down here.

705
00:58:44,567 --> 00:58:47,300
Hey, what's the matter? Huh?
You lookin' for someone?

706
00:58:47,300 --> 00:58:50,233
- Someone lookin' for you?
- ( Loud Growling )

707
00:58:51,200 --> 00:58:54,667
- There goes another one.
- Another what? What was that?

708
00:58:54,667 --> 00:58:56,700
Ah, the damn dog, Cerberus.

709
00:58:56,700 --> 00:59:02,700
He's supposed to guard the gate, keep
the dead down here where they belong.

710
00:59:02,700 --> 00:59:05,900
But he's gotten loose somehow. Now he's
running around all over, causing trouble.

711
00:59:05,900 --> 00:59:07,900
Aye, yay, yay, yay.

712
00:59:08,300 --> 00:59:13,833
Can't imagine what it must
be like up in the living world.

713
00:59:14,333 --> 00:59:17,267
Yeah. Well, I can.

714
00:59:20,267 --> 00:59:23,733
Uh, so, uh, how 'bout it?

715
00:59:23,733 --> 00:59:26,333
A little, uh, somethin' for the effort?

716
00:59:26,333 --> 00:59:28,333
Sorry. Can't help you.

717
00:59:28,833 --> 00:59:32,167
Hey. At least give me my lantern back.

718
00:59:32,167 --> 00:59:35,667
Maybe a little later.
Thanks for the ride, though.

719
00:59:35,667 --> 00:59:39,667
Oh, yeah! That's great!
Very funny. A real comedian.

720
00:59:40,133 --> 00:59:42,067
Why not pick on charon?
Everybody else does!

721
00:59:42,567 --> 00:59:45,833
BOATMAN: I don't know.
Times are tough. ( Muttering )

722
00:59:46,300 --> 00:59:49,200
Take a ride, don't pay you nothin'.

723
00:59:50,800 --> 00:59:53,233
( Distorted Voices Echoing )

724
00:59:57,233 --> 01:00:00,033
( Cerberus Growls,
Dead Person Scream )

725
01:00:14,267 --> 01:00:18,933
( Voices Whispering, Muttering )

726
01:00:22,533 --> 01:00:25,333
( Soft Thud, Clinking )

727
01:00:39,067 --> 01:00:40,767
Cerberus.

728
01:00:42,233 --> 01:00:43,700
( Growling )

