981
01:22:42,967 --> 01:22:44,567
Make him suffer, Hercules!

982
01:22:55,233 --> 01:22:58,067
( Snarling )

983
01:23:20,933 --> 01:23:23,433
- What's wrong?
- ( Cerberus Growling Softly )

984
01:23:32,367 --> 01:23:35,300
Pick it up! He'll kill you! Pick it up!

985
01:23:35,300 --> 01:23:36,300
( Snarling )

986
01:23:37,800 --> 01:23:39,300
Look.

987
01:23:41,300 --> 01:23:43,300
I don't want to hurt you.

988
01:23:48,133 --> 01:23:52,533
You just need to go back
to where you belong.

989
01:23:52,533 --> 01:23:54,533
( Barks )

990
01:23:54,533 --> 01:23:56,533
So what do you say?

991
01:24:06,900 --> 01:24:09,100
( Growling Softly, Sniffing )

992
01:24:09,100 --> 01:24:10,567
Will you go?

993
01:24:19,833 --> 01:24:22,767
( Whines )

994
01:24:27,200 --> 01:24:31,200
Remember that. Sometimes a
little kindness does the trick.

995
01:24:41,867 --> 01:24:43,267
( Exhales )

996
01:24:48,467 --> 01:24:50,067
Now stay.

997
01:24:51,667 --> 01:24:54,433
( Zapping )

998
01:24:55,233 --> 01:24:56,700
Deianeira.

999
01:24:59,533 --> 01:25:02,267
- Hercules.
- Deianeira!

1000
01:25:02,267 --> 01:25:05,033
I missed you. I missed you.

1001
01:25:07,033 --> 01:25:09,533
I wasn't gonna lose you.

1002
01:25:16,100 --> 01:25:18,100
( Roaring Stops )

1003
01:25:25,300 --> 01:25:27,800
MAN: He's done it!
Hercules has done it!

1004
01:25:28,300 --> 01:25:30,800
- The town's been saved!
- WOMAN: Our town's alive again.

1005
01:25:30,800 --> 01:25:32,300
You saved us, Hercules.

1006
01:25:32,300 --> 01:25:36,967
You saved our village, I don't know
what else to say except thank you.

1007
01:25:36,967 --> 01:25:38,467
You don't have to say
anything else.

1008
01:25:38,900 --> 01:25:43,600
- I--   - DEIANEIRA: You don't have
to say anything to me either.

1009
01:25:43,600 --> 01:25:47,433
You did what you had to do. Because
of it you saved a lot of lives.

1010
01:25:47,433 --> 01:25:49,567
I still feel like I owe you an apology.

1011
01:25:52,000 --> 01:25:55,133
So, uh, what are you
gonna do now, Iole?

1012
01:25:56,133 --> 01:25:59,333
I think Lycastus and I will
start a family of our own.

1013
01:25:59,733 --> 01:26:03,367
- If we can do half as well as you have--
- You'll do just fine.

1014
01:26:03,367 --> 01:26:05,367
I'm sure of it.

1015
01:26:05,867 --> 01:26:06,867
Thank you.

1016
01:26:26,600 --> 01:26:30,300
- Now... let's go home.
- ( Laughs )

1017
01:26:30,700 --> 01:26:33,133
- Thank you, Hercules!
- Hercules!

1018
01:26:35,933 --> 01:26:39,133
( Chickens Clucking, Dog Barking )

1019
01:26:42,733 --> 01:26:45,500
- HERCULES: How'd I do, kids?
- You got three!

1020
01:26:48,133 --> 01:26:53,500
Still wondering about
your... mortality?

1021
01:26:53,500 --> 01:26:56,233
- Should I be?
- I don't know.

1022
01:26:56,233 --> 01:27:00,100
Just because you came back from the
Underworld doesn't ment you're an immortal.

1023
01:27:00,600 --> 01:27:02,567
- Doesn't mean I'm not.
- True.

1024
01:27:02,567 --> 01:27:07,067
To tell you the truth, I don't think
I really care if I live forever.

1025
01:27:07,067 --> 01:27:10,067
Everything I need is right
here and now.

1026
01:27:10,067 --> 01:27:11,567
You've got a point.

1027
01:27:11,567 --> 01:27:15,067
I'm sure you feel the same way
if this were...

1028
01:27:15,567 --> 01:27:17,900
- My family.
- I heard that.

1029
01:27:17,900 --> 01:27:21,967
- What are you talking about? This is
your family.   - Thank you, thank you.

1030
01:27:22,367 --> 01:27:25,700
Grandfather, look. Look what I've got.

1031
01:27:26,200 --> 01:27:28,700
- Oh! What is that?
- An apple.

1032
01:27:28,700 --> 01:27:32,100
An apple, isn't that the nicest apple...

1033
01:27:32,100 --> 01:27:33,967
You've ever seen?

1034
01:27:33,967 --> 01:27:36,500
- Want a bite? Come on.
- ( Laughs )

1035
01:27:36,500 --> 01:27:39,200
- Hercules!
- ZEUS: Take a bite.

1036
01:27:39,200 --> 01:27:41,933
Hercules!

1037
01:27:44,033 --> 01:27:45,633
We need you!

1038
01:27:46,033 --> 01:27:47,400
Captioned by Grantman Brown

